# Git Deployment Workflow

These rules apply to this project, not to the old 360GS-SLAM reference project.

## Project mapping

- Local project root: `E:\Project\360Droid-splat`
- GitHub repository: `https://github.com/WillLan/360Droid-splat.git`
- Git remote name: `origin`
- Default branch: `main`
- Remote server: `50902` via `lanboyang@172.19.53.39`
- Remote project root: `/mnt/disk1/lanboyang/Project/360Droid-splat`
- Read-only reference source: `/mnt/disk1/lanboyang/Project/360GS-SLAM`

Never push, pull, clone, or deploy this project into
`/mnt/disk1/lanboyang/Project/360GS-SLAM`.  That directory is only a read-only
reference source.

## Local checks before commit

Run suitable lightweight checks before committing changed code.  For normal
Python changes, prefer:

```powershell
git status --short --branch
python -m compileall frontend mapping backend system tests
python -m pytest
```

## Upload workflow

1. Commit local changes with a clear message.
2. Ask the user to confirm before pushing.
3. Push only after confirmation:

   ```powershell
   git push origin main
   ```

## Remote update workflow

After a successful push, update only this mapped remote directory.

If the directory does not exist:

```bash
ssh lanboyang@172.19.53.39 'git clone https://github.com/WillLan/360Droid-splat.git /mnt/disk1/lanboyang/Project/360Droid-splat'
```

If the directory exists, inspect the worktree and only fast-forward pull when
it is clean:

```bash
ssh lanboyang@172.19.53.39 'cd /mnt/disk1/lanboyang/Project/360Droid-splat && git status --short && git pull --ff-only origin main'
```

If local uncommitted or untracked files block the pull, report them and stop.
Do not move, delete, overwrite, stash, or reset remote files unless the user
explicitly asks.

## Artifacts excluded from Git

Do not commit generated outputs, checkpoints, caches, or logs by default:
`outputs/`, `*.pt`, `*.pth`, `__pycache__/`, `.pytest_cache/`, `debug.log`, and
temporary run logs.

## Training launch

Pulling code does not imply launching training.  Start or restart experiments
only after a separate explicit user command.  Training launch must follow the
remote experiment safety rules: check RAM, swap, active Python jobs, and GPU
usage; run long jobs inside `tmux`; and use the `pfgs360` Python environment.

